  "texts": [
    "A Notations and Frequently Used Inequalities AppendixWe introduce some shorthand notations frequently used in the rest of the paper.",
    "The operators below abstract the (semi-)gradient of the leader, follower, mean field, and value functions.D(ω, µ, V l, s, b, s ′) = ∇ ω log ϕ ω (b | s) r l (s, b, µ) + γV l (s ′) -V l (s), F (θ, µ, V f, s, a, b, s ′) = ∇ θ log π θ (a | s) r f (s, a, b, µ) + τ E(π θ, s) + γV f (s ′) -V f (s), H(µ, s) = e s -µ, G l (ω, µ, V l, s, a, b, s ′) = e s r l (s, b, µ) + γV l (s ′) -V l (s), G f (θ, µ, V f, s, a, b, s ′) = e s r f (s, a, b, µ) + τ E(π θ, s) + γV f (s ′) -V f (s).",
    "(17)Given the notations in ( 17), we can re-write the variable updates in Algorithm 1.ω k+1 = ω k + ζ k D(ω k, μk, Vl,k, s k, b k, s ′ k),(18)θ k+1 = θ k + α k F (θ k, μk, Vf,k, s k, a k, b k, s ′ k),(19)μk+1 = Π ∆ S μk + ξ k H(μ k, sk),(20)Vl,k+1 = Π B V Vl,k + β k G l (ω k, μk, Vl,k, s k, a k, b k, s ′ k),(21)Vf,k+1 = Π B V Vf,k + β k G f (θ k, μk, Vf,k, s k, a k, b k, s ′ k).",
    "(22)We also define the expected versions of the (semi-)gradient operators, where the expectation is taken over the stochastic samples from the stationary distribution.D(ω, µ, V l) ≜ E s∼d π,ϕω,µ ρ,a∼π(•|s),b∼ϕω(•|s),s ′ ∼P µ (•|s,a,b) [D(ω, µ, V l, s, b, s ′)],(23)F (θ, ω, µ, V f) ≜ E s∼d π θ,ϕω,µ ρ,a∼π θ (•|s),b∼ϕω(•|s),s ′ ∼P µ (•|s,a,b) [F (θ, µ, V f, s, a, b, s ′)],(24)H(π, ω, µ) ≜ E s∼ν π,ϕω,µ [H(µ, s)], (25) Ḡl (ω, µ, V l) ≜ E s∼d π,ϕω,µ ρ,a∼π(•|s),b∼ϕω(•|s),s ′ ∼P µ (•|s,a,b) [G l (ω, µ, V l, s, a, b, s ′)],(26)Ḡf (θ, ω, µ, V f) ≜ E s∼d π θ,ϕω,µ ρ,a∼π θ (•|s),b∼ϕω(•|s),s ′ ∼P µ (•|s,a,b) [G f (θ, µ, V f, s, a, b, s ′)].",
    "(27)We re-iterate that due to the state separation discussed in Section 2, D and Ḡl are independent of the single follower's policy π, though π appears on the right hand side of ( 23) and ( 26).We define the filtrationF k = {s 0, a 0, b 0, s ′ 0 • • •, s k, a k, b k, s ′ k, s0, • • •, sk }.Unless otherwise noted, we use ∥ • ∥ to denote the ℓ 2 norm of a vector and the operator norm of a matrix.We may use ∇ ω Φ(ϕ ω) and ∇ ω J l (ϕ ω, µ ⋆ (ϕ ω)) interchangeably in the rest of the paper, which is the true gradient of the leader."
  ],
